<subSubSection id="C3616572FF88E462A8B55423456CF969" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC436F9FF88E462A8B55423456CF969" blockId="40.[151,1437,1540,2035]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B90FEAEBFF88E462A8B55423404DF984" bold="true" box="[199,334,1612,1637]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named in honor of Edith Folger Andrews (
<date id="FFC51039FF88E462AB8554234578F984" box="[1015,1147,1612,1637]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" value="1915" valueMax="2015">1915–2015</date>
), Nantucket naturalist, in whose yard (“Ice Pond Lot”) several of the specimens used in this study were collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
